title: Wedge product and determinant

We can use the exterior algebra to define the [[determinant|Determinante]]: If we have $$m$$ vectors $$v_j\in V$$ given in terms of the basis $$(e_1,\dots,e_m)$$ as $$\sum_i v_j^i,$$ then

$$
v_1 \wedge\dots\wedge v_m = \det(v_j^i)e_{1 2 \cdots m}.
$$